1
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>If anyone's leaving
it should be me.</i>

2
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>Don't let your
family fall apart.</i>

3
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,800
<i> You should not be separated.</i>

4
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:47,833
<i>It really hurts every time
I see that man.</i>

5
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:49,000
<i> It's just frustrating</i>

6
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,033
<i>because it feels like
they don't understand us.</i>

7
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:53,300
<i>Mom's siding with
Jessica and that man.</i>

8
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:54,700
<i> Let's just leave.</i>

9
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:55,567
<i> Jeff!</i>

10
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:56,633
<i> Jeff!</i>

11
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:58,333
<i>Sorry for bringing dad
and Jessica here.</i>

12
00:00:58,467 --> 00:00:59,567
<i> What good is your apology?</i>

13
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,733
<i>I wish I were just a baby
when your father left us.</i>

14
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:03,833
<i>So I didn't have to feel
the pain of being abandoned.</i>

15
00:01:03,967 --> 00:01:05,800
<i>For the sake of my godchildren,
I'm begging you.</i>

16
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:07,400
<i> Stop messing with them.</i>

17
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:12,700
<i>They don't even know how to get
along with your husband anymore!</i>

18
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:14,133
<i> To get along?</i>

19
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:15,367
<i> So I was right.</i>

20
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:17,300
<i>My husband and daughter
are at Felma's house.</i>

21
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:18,533
<i> Mom!</i>

22
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:19,633
<i> Mom!</i>

23
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,000
<i>- Jeff and Andrea are leaving.
- Be quiet.</i>

24
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:22,400
<i> Mom will hear you!</i>

25
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:23,567
<i> That's what they want.</i>

26
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:24,767
<i> Let's just let them be.</i>

27
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:25,967
<i>- You're being annoying.
- Tell Felma to come out!</i>

28
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,700
<i>- Hey! You can't!
- I know she's here Felma,</i>

29
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,933
<i>bring out my husband
and my child!</i>

30
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:32,033
<i>- My employer's not here!
- What's going on here?</i>

31
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,467
<i> Hold on. Why are you filming?</i>

32
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,167
<i>- I told you, I'm a cop.
- Stop it!</i>

33
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,967
<i>Why? Are you scared that the
whole world will find out</i>

34
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:40,467
<i>you're hiding my
husband and child?</i>

35
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,167
<i>- There!
- What?</i>

36
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,500
<i>- There!
- Stop it!</i>

37
00:01:42,633 --> 00:01:43,933
<i>She kidnapped my husband
and child!</i>

38
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,500
<i> Stop!</i>

39
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:46,933
<i>- Hazel!
- You'll get hurt!</i>

40
00:01:47,067 --> 00:01:48,200
<i> Hazel, that's enough!</i>

41
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,600
<i> Don't hurt them!</i>

42
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:01,400
What about your work
in Aunt Felma's business?

43
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,433
I won't come to work anymore.

44
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:07,933
How can we work together
when we don't get along?

45
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,033
Don't worry.

46
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:13,567
I'll look for a
new job right away.

47
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:14,967
So I can help you
with the expenses.

48
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:17,933
That's not what I'm worried
about, Jeff.

49
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:21,467
I'm worried about you
and your family.

50
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:25,200
It's tough when you have issues
that never get resolved.

51
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,067
Maybe this is the solution.

52
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,933
Maybe we should give
each other some space.

53
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,933
Daisy, I'm sorry
for the trouble.

54
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,400
It's okay.

55
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:46,333
At least Tetay will have
someone with her

56
00:02:46,467 --> 00:02:47,533
whenever I'm at work.

57
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:50,833
I don't need to look for someone
who will watch over her,

58
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,833
especially since I'm about
to start my night shift.

59
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,200
There.

60
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:57,833
I'll take care of our kid.

61
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:01,333
I promise you, I won't be
a burden to you and Tetay.

62
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,167
Manuel?

63
00:03:09,167 --> 00:03:10,500
Jessica?

64
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,700
Finally.

65
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,400
I miss you so much.

66
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:28,633
Hazel, stop!

67
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:30,733
Don't hurt Manuel!

68
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:31,933
Don't hurt Manuel!

69
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:33,633
How dare you!

70
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:35,967
You even brought my
daughter with you!

71
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:39,833
You used Jessica just to
get back with this woman?

72
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,600
Stop!

73
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:44,167
Who are you?

74
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:47,233
Stop getting involved
in our marital problems.

75
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,633
Our marriage!

76
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,333
Only between us!

77
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,600
Come on, Felma.

78
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:56,967
After all these years,
you still don't get it?

79
00:03:57,533 --> 00:03:58,767
I'm the one he married.

80
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,067
I'm the wife.

81
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,567
That's why I'm the real
Mrs. Cruz!

82
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:02,967
Mommy, can you please stop?

83
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:06,200
Aunt Felma and daddy
did nothing wrong.

84
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,167
I'm the one who wanted us
to stay here.

85
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:10,233
In fact, I love it here!

86
00:04:10,633 --> 00:04:11,633
Really?

87
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:12,700
Hazel!

88
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,333
Stop it!

89
00:04:14,933 --> 00:04:17,233
Give your daughter
a little dignity!

90
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:18,700
Come on.

91
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,800
Don't hurt your child!

92
00:04:20,933 --> 00:04:22,567
They're fine here already!

93
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:25,667
- Just leave them alone!
- Why do you keep meddling?

94
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:27,400
You're not family!

95
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,633
You're just a mistress!

96
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,067
Do you get that? You're just
the other woman!

97
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,233
Have you no shame?

98
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:32,467
Maximo!

99
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,333
Quick, help me!

100
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:34,833
Forget her already!

101
00:04:34,967 --> 00:04:37,167
No! You can't do that!

102
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,000
Help me!

103
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:41,133
Don't hurt Manuel!

104
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:42,633
Mom! Mom!

105
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:10,433
Come on, Andrea, seriously.

106
00:05:11,167 --> 00:05:12,667
Why did you have to run away?

107
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:16,500
Did it really have
to come to this?

108
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:19,233
What about Felma now?

109
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:22,133
She's probably worried sick
about you and Jeffrey.

110
00:05:22,267 --> 00:05:28,267
And, Andrea, watch your mouth
when you talk to your mother.

111
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,133
You talk back too much.

112
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,000
This hurts me too, you know.

113
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:37,933
All my life,
I've been with my mother.

114
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,467
And then, in an instant,
we're being torn apart.

115
00:05:44,433 --> 00:05:46,100
I don't want to hurt her.

116
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,400
I don't want to be
disrespectful either.

117
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:53,867
But every time I see that man,
I can't help but feel angry.

118
00:06:02,967 --> 00:06:07,067
I only came here
to get some space.

119
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,667
I just needed to breathe.

120
00:06:15,633 --> 00:06:22,400
So, please, Auntie, I hope you
won't tell my mom that I'm here.

121
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:31,667
I'm not staying long.

122
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:34,600
I'll find somewhere else to go
right away.

123
00:06:52,367 --> 00:06:53,633
You have no shame!

124
00:06:53,767 --> 00:06:55,367
You're so vulgar!

125
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,867
Hey! Wait!

126
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,833
- Let go of me!
- Hazel!

127
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,533
Don't hurt my mom!

128
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:01,267
What do you mean,
"don't hurt her?"

129
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:02,833
- What about...
- Manuel!

130
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:04,800
You see this?
You're all so disrespectful!

131
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:05,967
They're my husband and daughter!

132
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:08,300
I'm taking them with me,
whether you like it or not!

133
00:07:08,433 --> 00:07:09,767
- Come on, let's go. Come on.
- No! No!

134
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:10,667
- Mom, no!
- No!

135
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,667
- Let me go!
- Get out of here!

136
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,200
- Guard!
- Hazel!

137
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:15,967
- Why are you stopping me?
- Guard!

138
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:16,900
Let's go!

139
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:18,867
- Hazel!
- Leave!

140
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,867
I got this!

141
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,867
I'm a cop!

142
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,433
Wait. Aren't you the one

143
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:23,733
who's supposed to be picking
someone up?

144
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:25,467
Bring them out!

145
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,433
We're not leaving.

146
00:07:27,567 --> 00:07:28,867
Didn't you hear me?

147
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,800
They're my family!

148
00:07:30,933 --> 00:07:32,267
Why are they even here?

149
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,467
You don't want to leave?

150
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,333
Fine.

151
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,567
We're calling the police.

152
00:07:37,267 --> 00:07:38,567
The real police!

153
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:39,767
If you don't leave,

154
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:42,100
I'll have you charged
with trespassing and assault!

155
00:07:42,233 --> 00:07:44,067
Fine, then! Go ahead and sue me.

156
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,767
And if I sue you instead?

157
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:47,200
We're not leaving, got it?

158
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:48,533
We're not leaving.

159
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:49,967
That's my husband!

160
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,200
That's my child!

161
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:52,733
Bring them out now.

162
00:07:52,867 --> 00:07:54,300
Guard, please get them out now.

163
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,867
- Hey! Don't touch me!
- Go ahead.

164
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,767
Hey! Remember this!

165
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:58,867
Stop!

166
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,300
I'll do whatever it takes

167
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:02,067
to get my husband
and daughter back.

168
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,467
They're my family,
do you understand?

169
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:08,300
- I told you, don't touch me!
- Hold her! Restrain her!

170
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:28,467
Thank you.

171
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:39,800
Felma, I apologize
for what Hazel did.

172
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,233
Forget about that.

173
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:50,933
What matters is that
she didn't get you and Jessica.

174
00:08:51,067 --> 00:08:51,933
Does it still hurt?

175
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:56,233
Maybe you need
to take some medicine.

176
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:04,533
What hurts more are the
things happening, Manuel.

177
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,867
I just realized
that it's not easy

178
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,667
to let go of Jeffrey and Andrea.

179
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:17,000
Even though they're
already at the right age,

180
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:20,767
they're still the babies
I carried.

181
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:23,100
Let's just go back
to the original plan.

182
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:26,600
Jessica and I will leave
so they can come back here.

183
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:28,267
No.

184
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,600
That won't happen.

185
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:37,500
As for me, I just hope
they'll trust my decision.

186
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,933
Just because they've grown up,

187
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:46,400
doesn't mean they can now ignore
me as their mother.

188
00:09:48,067 --> 00:09:49,567
But it has already happened.

189
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:55,600
My only prayer is that
they're doing okay.

190
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:57,400
Wherever they are now.

191
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:08,433
Really, Dad? You're going
to live here now?

192
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:11,900
Dad's going to live here!

193
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:16,900
What about grandmother?

194
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:18,633
What did she say?

195
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:21,500
Did she agree that
you'll live here?

196
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:26,833
To be honest, mom doesn't
know that I'm here.

197
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,633
You didn't ask permission, Dad?

198
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,500
Did you run away?

199
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,967
Isn't running away wrong?

200
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:36,433
What's the problem?

201
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:38,667
Tetay, don't ask
too many questions.

202
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:42,900
Let's just be glad that your dad
is with us.

203
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:46,267
You'll eat together,
sleep together.

204
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,467
And anytime you need me,
I'll be here.

205
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,633
So don't tell your grandmother,
okay?

206
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,467
So our time together
can last longer, all right?

207
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,367
- Okay?
- Okay, Dad.

208
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,067
Approved! Come here!

209
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,933
We'll be all together, Mom.

210
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:00,867
Come on, Mom!

211
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:02,733
Don't be shy.

212
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,567
Weren't you a cop before?

213
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:12,067
You're used to fights
and shootouts.

214
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:13,800
So what happened?

215
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:16,167
You couldn't even
bring Manuel with you.

216
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:18,033
What do you want me to do?

217
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:19,433
Hit those women?

218
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:21,033
They're still too young.

219
00:11:21,167 --> 00:11:22,433
One of them's even your kid.

220
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:26,433
Besides, classmate,
I'm a gentleman.

221
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:29,700
Can you just pay me?

222
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:31,600
My phone got broken.

223
00:11:33,267 --> 00:11:35,667
It wouldn't have broken
if you hadn't been so stupid.

224
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,700
You're going too far!

225
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,533
I'm already letting you
boss me around,

226
00:11:39,667 --> 00:11:41,333
even if you're hitting
below the belt.

227
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,567
If only we hadn't had
that MU back then.

228
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:44,367
Hey!

229
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,400
What MU are you talking about?

230
00:11:46,533 --> 00:11:47,567
Get lost!

231
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:48,800
Yes, I'm leaving!

232
00:11:48,933 --> 00:11:50,733
And don't you ever call me
again!

233
00:11:51,167 --> 00:11:52,833
I won't! Because you don't even
have a phone!

234
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:53,600
Get lost!

235
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:55,367
So annoying!

236
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:03,700
So what now, friend?

237
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:05,767
How are you going to get
your husband and daughter back?

238
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,000
There's still another way.

239
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:11,933
How's that lawyer
I asked you to find?

240
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:21,367
Andeng, just put your clothes
in Mayette's cabinet.

241
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,433
It's already empty.

242
00:12:23,567 --> 00:12:25,867
She gave away all her clothes
before she went abroad.

243
00:12:27,267 --> 00:12:28,433
She's lucky.

244
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:31,500
She's far away
from all this trouble.

245
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:36,567
Speaking of trouble,
I mentioned to that little dwarf

246
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:39,133
that your dad's at your house.

247
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:42,833
She's definitely
going to make a mess.

248
00:12:44,033 --> 00:12:46,000
See?

249
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:48,600
You're worried
about your mom, too.

250
00:12:50,667 --> 00:12:51,667
No, Auntie.

251
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:55,367
That was mom's choice.

252
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:58,233
That's what she decided.

253
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:01,967
She should face
the consequences.

254
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:10,033
You know, I have a story
to tell you.

255
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:17,467
When Mayette decided to go
to Hong Kong,

256
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:21,233
of course, your uncle and I
were really sad.

257
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,067
Especially since your
Uncle Abel had just come back

258
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,600
from Saudi Arabia.

259
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:32,833
I thought, for the first time,
our family would be whole.

260
00:13:33,767 --> 00:13:34,633
But it didn't happen.

261
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:37,400
The opportunity was there.

262
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:40,767
And she decided to go abroad.

263
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,500
Even if I wanted to stop her,
I couldn't.

264
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:46,000
Because that's what
would make her happy.

265
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,300
But here's the question, Andeng.

266
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:53,567
When you left,
were you really happy?

267
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,500
I'm telling you,

268
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:03,367
no matter how harsh the words
you heard from your mom were,

269
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:05,667
she's hurting.

270
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,633
Two of her children left.

271
00:14:08,767 --> 00:14:09,833
You and Jeff.

272
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:24,467
Oh, Andeng.

273
00:14:31,533 --> 00:14:36,367
This is Atty. Nico Salazar,
the lawyer my uncle recommended.

274
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,400
He's an expert
on the Family Code.

275
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:41,200
Attorney, this is the friend
I was telling you about.

276
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,367
Hazel.

277
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,867
Nice meeting you, Ma'am.

278
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:45,967
Likewise, Attorney.

279
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,233
Come on, let's sit down.

280
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:53,867
Well, I've been looking forward
to seeing you, Attorney.

281
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:56,067
I'll get straight to the point.

282
00:14:57,767 --> 00:14:59,300
I want to file a case
against my husband

283
00:14:59,433 --> 00:15:01,033
for kidnapping my daughter.

284
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:03,233
And against his mistress, too.

285
00:15:04,467 --> 00:15:05,867
I want them both in jail.

286
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:13,733
How's my princess?

287
00:15:13,867 --> 00:15:15,300
I'm good, Grandmother.

288
00:15:15,433 --> 00:15:16,167
How about you?

289
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:23,400
I'm sad, Dear.

290
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:26,067
I'm worried about your dad.

291
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:28,767
Is he there?

292
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:34,833
I'm not allowed to tell you,
but it's also wrong to lie.

293
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,933
Right?

294
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:38,167
<i> So I'll tell you the truth.</i>

295
00:15:38,467 --> 00:15:40,233
Dad's here.

296
00:15:40,367 --> 00:15:42,867
So don't be sad, Grandmother.

297
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:47,133
Careful, Dad.

298
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:49,600
Thank you.

299
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:01,533
Hello, Bro?

300
00:16:01,667 --> 00:16:04,333
Bro, good news.

301
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:06,400
Andrea's here with us.

302
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:07,467
Really?

303
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,133
Andeng stayed there?

304
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:11,767
Oh, thank goodness.

305
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:14,833
Bro, I'll leave my daughter
in your care for now, okay?

306
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:17,633
And sorry for the trouble.

307
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:18,900
Yeah, it's all good, Bro.

308
00:16:19,033 --> 00:16:21,633
I just called you over
so you wouldn't worry.

309
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:24,500
Thank you so, so much, bro.

310
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,867
What you're doing
really means a lot.

311
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:29,967
All right, I'd better go
before she notices or hears us.

312
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:32,200
Okay, thanks again.

313
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:35,467
Dad, let's tell Aunt Felma.

314
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:37,233
Hold on, sweetheart.

315
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:42,067
What if we go see your sister?

316
00:16:42,667 --> 00:16:45,200
Since I'm the reason things
got messed up between them,

317
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,000
I should be the one to fix it.

318
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:49,033
Dad, I'm not sure.

319
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:51,400
This could make things
even more complicated.

320
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:54,300
Dear, I'm not completely sure
about this either.

321
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,533
But it's better than
not trying at all.

322
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:02,233
I want to help your Aunt Felma.

323
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:06,400
And if I have to beg Andrea just
so they can make peace, I will.

324
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:21,200
Why aren't you asleep yet?

325
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:27,067
I'm just still adjusting,
Auntie.

326
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:30,867
Because you had always been
with your mom your whole life.

327
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,433
You were always
right beside her.

328
00:17:33,567 --> 00:17:35,400
She was always right
beside me, Auntie.

329
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:39,133
I remember...

330
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:44,200
when I had surgery.

331
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:50,067
She never left my side.

332
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:53,767
<i>I was asleep, but she never
let go of my hand.</i>

333
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:57,567
<i>Every time I woke up,
she was still there.</i>

334
00:17:58,067 --> 00:18:00,467
<i>Even when she was tired,
she was sleepy...</i>

335
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,500
she never left.

336
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:08,000
Not like her former husband.

337
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,700
Who, turns out, was never
really her husband at all.

338
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:20,800
Why is it like that, Auntie?

339
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,533
The moment that man came back
into our lives,

340
00:18:25,967 --> 00:18:27,333
mom seemed to have forgotten

341
00:18:27,467 --> 00:18:29,300
everything we went through
together.

342
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:38,067
Andeng, of course,
it wasn't nothing.

343
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,767
You can't just brush that aside.

344
00:18:44,067 --> 00:18:48,100
Did you know,
even before you were born,

345
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:52,200
your mom was already creating
beautiful memories with you?

346
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:58,600
When she was pregnant with you,
she was so excited.

347
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:01,700
"I hope it's a baby girl."

348
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:05,767
So she went out and bought all
these colorful little clothes.

349
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:10,700
Your mom was so excited
to finally meet you.

350
00:19:13,667 --> 00:19:16,700
Andeng, your mom loves you.

351
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:19,200
So, so much.

352
00:19:24,467 --> 00:19:26,500
I love her so much, too, Auntie.

353
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:31,400
But maybe that's just how it is.

354
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:37,467
She'd rather be a good person
to others

355
00:19:38,567 --> 00:19:40,800
than be a good mother to me.

356
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:58,633
I have parental rights too,
Attorney, since I'm the mother.

357
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:01,133
And besides,
Jessica is still a minor.

358
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:02,967
Shouldn't she be with me?

359
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:11,000
Waiter, excuse me.

360
00:20:13,967 --> 00:20:17,200
Can I have one more slice
of carrot cake, please?

361
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:18,467
Yes, Sir.

362
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:20,233
Thank you.

363
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:26,600
Attorney?

364
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:29,533
Yes?

365
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:33,100
Ma'am, you do have the right
to take custody of your child.

366
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:37,500
But only if we can prove

367
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:42,167
that your husband lacks the
capacity to be a good father.

368
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:44,600
So what can I do then?

369
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:47,600
You can file for a custody

370
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,567
so that Jessica is legally
placed under your care.

371
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:53,033
And once the child is with you,

372
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:59,300
we can make it appear that
he kidnapped your daughter.

373
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:08,267
Andrea's safe now.

374
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,200
Abel said he'll
take care of her.

375
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:14,833
At least we know Jeff
is with Daisy.

376
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:16,833
We no longer have to worry.

377
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,200
That's what's important.

378
00:21:20,167 --> 00:21:21,500
Let them calm down.

379
00:21:23,267 --> 00:21:24,767
I talked to Tetay.

380
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:27,733
She said she'll find a way
for us to talk.

381
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:29,767
I really hope you reconcile
with them.

382
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:31,767
So they can come back here.

383
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,000
What about Andrea?

384
00:21:34,133 --> 00:21:35,500
I'll talk to her.

385
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:39,500
But maybe not just yet.

386
00:21:40,033 --> 00:21:42,733
You know how your
sister is, right?

387
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,367
She's too stubborn.

388
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:48,333
She needs time to
think things through.

389
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:50,833
We'll talk eventually.

390
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:55,667
I could never really stay mad
at your siblings.

391
00:21:57,467 --> 00:21:58,733
I love them so much.

392
00:22:00,933 --> 00:22:04,433
Ma'am, I got a text from Jeff.

393
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,000
What did he say?

394
00:22:06,133 --> 00:22:10,367
He's asking if I can pack up
the rest of Andrea's things.

395
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,667
Should I do it?

396
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,967
Can't we just file a kidnapping
case against him right away?

397
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:27,433
Well, Ma'am...

398
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,600
It's not that simple.

399
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:31,433
What about Felma, the mistress?

400
00:22:31,567 --> 00:22:32,967
What case can I file
against her?

401
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:35,133
She's enabling what Manuel did!

402
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:36,633
Is there anything I can file
against her?

403
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:41,600
Carrot cake, Sir.

404
00:22:41,733 --> 00:22:42,500
Thank you.

405
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,467
So?

406
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:55,667
So, Attorney?

407
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:56,667
Yes?

408
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,233
Accessory to the crime.

409
00:22:59,933 --> 00:23:06,300
But only after you get
full custody of the child.

410
00:23:06,767 --> 00:23:08,300
That could take forever,
Attorney.

411
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:10,333
At this rate, my daughter
might turn 18,

412
00:23:10,467 --> 00:23:12,167
and the case still won't have
moved forward!

413
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:16,833
Girl, once Jessica turns 18,

414
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:19,267
it'll be even harder for you
to get her back from Manuel.

415
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,333
Ma'am...

416
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,100
I just have a suggestion.

417
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:33,433
Maybe you could talk things
over with your husband.

418
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:40,567
Because we advocate for keeping
families together,

419
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:43,100
rather than being apart.

420
00:23:44,167 --> 00:23:46,867
Attorney, that's exactly
what I want.

421
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:49,167
So please help me.

422
00:23:50,033 --> 00:23:52,200
Help me get my family back.

423
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:01,200
Darn it!

424
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:05,433
I even spent 5,000 pesos
on that consultation

425
00:24:05,567 --> 00:24:07,167
with the lawyer and got nothing
out of it.

426
00:24:07,867 --> 00:24:09,167
You got something, girl.

427
00:24:09,300 --> 00:24:11,600
At least now you know
what cases you can file

428
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:13,900
against Felma and Manuel.

429
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:16,433
Really? You heard
what the lawyer said!

430
00:24:17,333 --> 00:24:18,700
Manuel could just defend himself

431
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:20,067
by saying I'm the one
hurting them.

432
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:23,200
And if that happens,

433
00:24:23,333 --> 00:24:25,200
how am I supposed to file a
kidnapping case against them?

434
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:30,467
I even spent 75,000 pesos!

435
00:24:30,633 --> 00:24:31,500
Can you imagine?

436
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:33,500
That was just for
the acceptance fee.

437
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:35,133
The hearing fees

438
00:24:35,267 --> 00:24:36,133
and all the other charges
aren't even included!

439
00:24:36,267 --> 00:24:38,867
What kind of lawyer did
you recommend to me?

440
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,233
So expensive.

441
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,067
I can't afford
something like that.

442
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,367
I'm not going to drain
my savings for it.

443
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,133
Right now, I'm even
looking for a job.

444
00:24:47,467 --> 00:24:51,133
The salary has to match
my credentials as a nurse.

445
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:54,433
So, you're just going
to give up, friend?

446
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:56,567
Don't make the same mistake
I committed.

447
00:24:57,367 --> 00:24:59,867
I didn't fight for Charles
when he filed for divorce.

448
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,600
Well, it's your fault.

449
00:25:04,533 --> 00:25:06,267
You let him catch you
with another man.

450
00:25:08,367 --> 00:25:10,100
It was just a fling.

451
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:12,700
Charles is the one I love.

452
00:25:13,433 --> 00:25:16,933
So if you love Manuel,
fight for him.

453
00:25:18,933 --> 00:25:21,400
All I want is for Manuel
and Felma to be scared

454
00:25:21,533 --> 00:25:23,167
that I'm going to sue them.

455
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:25,067
Because if that happens,

456
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:28,000
that woman will just willingly
give up my husband and daughter.

457
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,600
Want some milk tea?

458
00:25:36,733 --> 00:25:41,100
There's a coffee shop nearby
that has the best milk teas.

459
00:25:41,233 --> 00:25:42,333
Sure.

460
00:25:42,467 --> 00:25:45,000
Mommy, what are you doing here?

461
00:25:45,133 --> 00:25:46,433
We just want to talk to you.

462
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:49,100
Maybe it's better
if we talk in the van.

463
00:25:49,233 --> 00:25:51,300
Can we just forget about
our issues with mom for now?

464
00:25:51,433 --> 00:25:53,467
Let's focus on exposing
Hazel's lies instead.

465
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:54,600
Okay, fine.

466
00:25:54,733 --> 00:25:57,633
In the next live stream
of Karla Talakera and Hazel,

467
00:25:57,767 --> 00:25:59,433
I'll spill everything
in the comments

468
00:25:59,567 --> 00:26:02,733
about what her husband did
to our family.

469
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,900
That'll just hurt mom even more.

470
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:04,967
Are you going to hurt her?

471
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,733
If that's what it takes.

472
00:26:06,867 --> 00:26:07,767
Andrea, I'm telling you,

473
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:08,500
I'm the one you'll be up against
if you do that.

474
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:09,833
You'll lose a brother.

475
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,000
Fine, then.

476
00:26:11,133 --> 00:26:14,167
Stay with mom, Coleen,
and your father!

477
00:26:15,033 --> 00:26:16,633
Why hasn't Manuel called?

478
00:26:16,767 --> 00:26:19,233
Isn't he scared of
my threat to sue?

479
00:26:19,467 --> 00:26:20,900
As if you'd actually
follow through.

480
00:26:21,033 --> 00:26:23,133
You can't even afford a lawyer.

481
00:26:23,833 --> 00:26:26,167
Manuel, why is that woman here?

482
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:27,233
Where's Jessica?

483
00:26:27,367 --> 00:26:29,100
She's part of what
we need to discuss.

484
00:26:29,233 --> 00:26:31,400
This is just between you and me.

485
00:26:31,533 --> 00:26:32,500
Who are these people?

486
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:33,900
Atty. Butch Yeban.

487
00:26:34,033 --> 00:26:36,700
I represent Miss Felma Ruiz
in all present

488
00:26:36,833 --> 00:26:38,300
and forthcoming legal matters.

489
00:26:38,433 --> 00:26:39,733
And I'm Atty. Aries Tulio,

490
00:26:39,867 --> 00:26:42,300
legal counsel
for Mr. Manuel Cruz.
